  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Key legal elements typically include:\n\n1. Concealing the source of funds\n2. Transforming illegal proceeds into seemingly legitimate assets\n3. Attempting to disguise the origin of criminally derived money\n\nSpecific legal definitions vary by jurisdiction, but most include:\n- Intentional hiding of money from illegal activities\n- Conducting financial transactions to obscure criminal origins\n- Attempting to make illegally obtained funds appear legitimate\n\nI aim to provide factual legal information, not advice about financial activities.",
